<div class= "Clairmont-Dining community">
    <h1>Clairmont Dining</h1>
    <h3 style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://clairmontdining.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration: none;">Website Link</a></h3>
    <br>

    <div class= "DescAndVid">

    <div class= "Clairmont-Description">
        
        <p>
            Clairmont Dining was a project that I took up during my final year of undergrad in order to address a need at Emory Universityâ€™s Clairmont Campus. The Clairmont Campus is a residential area, about a half mile away from the main campus, where 3rd and 4th year students live. 
        </p>
        
        <p>
            Clairmont has a group of dorm buildings, a small rec center, and a cafeteria. The main downside of the location is that it is far away from any shops or restaurants, and the cafeteria is always crowded. Students would wait in a long line to make an order at a small counter and receive a ticket number in return. They would then wait in a cramped lobby area for their order number to be called out. On any given weekday the wait time at the Clairmont Cafe would be 15-30 minutes, and during peak hours it could easily climb to 40-60 minutes. 
        </p>
        
        <p>
           Many students complained about the wait times, but nothing changed. Eventually, I got fed up with this whole ordeal, and I decided to make a food ordering app so that students wouldn't have to wait in this absurd line every evening. To show the dining administration that this was a real issue, I visited every apartment door at the Clairmont Campus and got 105 students to sign a petition to institute an ordering app for the Clairmont Cafe. Over the course of 3 weeks, I taught myself how to use WordPress in order to make a dynamic ordering website that was easy to access and operate. This way, I could build and deploy the site quickly, and it would be easy to use and update for someone who didn't know programming.
        </p>
        
        
        <p>
            Once I finished the website, I set up a meeting with the Campus Dining Director and his boss, the Director of Campus Life. The meeting went well, and they asked me to work with them over the summer to help implement the website into their system. When I tried to set up another meeting to discuss the details of the integration, the Dining Director notified me that the university decided to move forward with a different ordering service that had been implemented in a number of other college campuses. Even though the university did not implement my website, I still felt like I advanced the goal of improving the dining experience for students on campus. 
        </p>
        

        <p>
           Unfortunately, when I visited the Clairmont Cafe a year afterwards, I found out that the university never introduced the other ordering service, and students were still waiting in long lines for dinner. I hope other students are able to get together and convince the administration to institute a better dining experience on the Clairmont Campus in the future. 
        </p>
        
        <p>
            The website is still active and you can access it <a href="https://clairmontdining.com/" target="_blank">here</a>.
        </p>

    </div>

